<paragraph blockId="15.[189,1399,612,814]" pageId="15" pageNumber="62">
WING (
<figureCitation box="[274,378,612,639]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[190,233,1922,1948]" captionTargetBox="[191,1397,487,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-76@14.[189,1397,487,1884]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 4. Amblypsilopus friedmani sp. nov. A–E. Holotype, ♂ (SMNHTAU). F–G. Paratype, ♂ (SMNHTAU). A. Habitus. B. Head. C. Antenna. D. Fore tarsomeres 2–5. E. Wing. F. Hypopygium, left lateral view, reflected light. G. Distoventral appendages of hypopygium, transmitted light." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4983314" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4983314/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="62">Fig. 4 E</figureCitation>
). Weakly widened distally, almost hyaline, veins brown; R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1088,1115,631,645]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="62">4+5</subScript>
gently curved to M 
<quantity box="[1357,1399,612,645]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="15" pageNumber="62" unit="in" value="1.0">
<subScript attach="left" box="[1357,1366,631,645]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="62">1</subScript>
in
</quantity>
apical third; M straight in basal half, slightly convex anteriad in middle part; M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1162,1171,666,680]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="62">1</subScript>
with strong elbow, forming right angle with M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[516,543,701,715]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="62">1+2</subScript>
; ratio of parts of costa between R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[950,977,701,715]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="62">2+3</subScript>
and R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1056,1083,701,715]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="62">4+5</subScript>
to those between R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1320,1347,701,715]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="62">4+5</subScript>
and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[215,224,736,750]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="62">1</subScript>
, 4/1; crossvein dm-m straight; ratio of crossvein dm-m to apical part of M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1100,1127,736,750]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="62">1+2</subScript>
(fork-handle) to apical part of M4, 0.74/1.13/0.37; anal vein weak; anal lobe well developed; anal angle acute; lower calypter yellow, with brown cilia; halter yellow with brown knob.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[189,1399,612,814]" box="[366,393,666,680]" pageId="15" pageNumber="62">
<subScript attach="left" box="[366,393,666,680]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="62">1+2</subScript>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[188,1400,853,1162]" pageId="15" pageNumber="62">
ABDOMEN. Thin, mostly shining blue-green, with short black hairs and long marginal setae; segment 1 yellow, with white and dark hairs; segments 2–3 orange, brown along distal margin; pregenital segments combined two times as long as mesonotum; hypopygium (
<figureCitation box="[879,966,924,950]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[190,233,1922,1948]" captionTargetBox="[191,1397,487,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-76@14.[189,1397,487,1884]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 4. Amblypsilopus friedmani sp. nov. A–E. Holotype, ♂ (SMNHTAU). F–G. Paratype, ♂ (SMNHTAU). A. Habitus. B. Head. C. Antenna. D. Fore tarsomeres 2–5. E. Wing. F. Hypopygium, left lateral view, reflected light. G. Distoventral appendages of hypopygium, transmitted light." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4983314" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4983314/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="62">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
) brown, with black hypandrium and yellow cercus; cercus with moderately broad neck and 2 long filiform arms and one very long seta between arms; dorsal arm of cercus covered with light setae dorsally, with one very long apical seta; ventral arm of cercus with 5–7 short apical and subapical setae; surstylus (
<figureCitation box="[1088,1183,1029,1056]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[190,233,1922,1948]" captionTargetBox="[191,1397,487,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-76@14.[189,1397,487,1884]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 4. Amblypsilopus friedmani sp. nov. A–E. Holotype, ♂ (SMNHTAU). F–G. Paratype, ♂ (SMNHTAU). A. Habitus. B. Head. C. Antenna. D. Fore tarsomeres 2–5. E. Wing. F. Hypopygium, left lateral view, reflected light. G. Distoventral appendages of hypopygium, transmitted light." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4983314" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4983314/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="62">Fig. 4G</figureCitation>
) broad, projected, bilobed; dorsal arm of surstylus deeply cleft, with 2–3 apical and subapical setae on each lobe; ventral arm of surstylus small, finger-like, with 2 small setae apically; epandrial lobe small, triangular, with 1 basal, 1 median and 1 apical seta.
</paragraph>
